        "ans_top4_original_only__small_gate_60_90": "The clustering algorithm is based on Gaussian Mixture Models (GMMs), and the primary challenge is the high dimensionality of vector embeddings, which can cause distance metrics to behave poorly in high-dimensional spaces. To address this, the paper employs Uniform Manifold Approximation and Projection (UMAP) for dimensionality reduction. Additionally, while the Gaussian assumption may not perfectly match the sparse and skewed distribution of text data, empirical results suggest it remains effective for the task."
