            15.1484375
        ],
        "ans_top4_original_only__small_gate_60_90": "The pseudocode for step 5 of the tree traversal method is implemented within the loop structure of the `TRAVERSE_TREE` algorithm, iterating over each layer from 0 to `tree.num_layers - 1` (i.e., `d` layers). For each layer, it computes the cosine similarity between the query and each node in the current set `S_current`, selects the top-k nodes with the highest scores, and updates `S_current` to this new set for the next iteration. The core pseudocode is:\n\n```python\nfor layer in range(tree.num_layers):\n    top_k = []\n    for node in S_current:\n        score = dot_product(query, node)\n        top_k.append((node, score))\n    S_layer = sorted(top_k)[:k].nodes\n    S_current = S_layer\n```\n\nThis process recursively generates sets $ S_1, S_2, \\dots, S_d $, as described in the text."
